line_1: Nor Charm, nor Art, nor Force avails.
line_2: The more he trys, the more he fails;

line_1: Ye Sons of Men, here nought avails
line_2: Your Strength, here all your Wisdom fails;

line_1: Whether we sleep or wake, it naught avails.
line_2: Against ill Luck all cunning Foresight fails;

line_1: Nor Maud's imperial rights, nor valour aught avails.
line_2: The tyrant's power at length prevails,
